<plot>Visits master cellist Gregor Piatigorsky at his home where he spends a typical day strolling through his garden, talking to his wife, working with his students, and playing the cello. Interviewed shortly before his death at age seventy-three, he reveals his graceful acceptance of aging, his genuine affection for his students, and his passionate devotion to his music.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?036527</url></doc>
